OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781111161
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to rule out tax hikes
OL,4,Cto fund defence spending
OL,6,FHe argued that the UK was leading on
OL,7,Fdefence, referencing the so-called
OL,8,Fcoalition of the willing.
OL,10,FBadenoch hit back, claiming that
OL,11,FStarmer won't cut welfare "because he
OL,12,Fis too weak to stand up for our
OL,13,Fnational security".
OL,15,FStarmer again pointed to the record of
OL,16,Fthe previous government and said:
OL,17,F"Defence spending went down, welfare
OL,18,Fspending went up #88 billion overall,
OL,19,Fon their watch, #33 billion under the
OL,20,Fshadow chancellor."
OL,26,@yD@AOU|D@SO]
