OL,3,CStarmer refuses to rule out tax hikes
OL,4,Cto fund defence spending
OL,6,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,7,Fraised concerns that the hospital
OL,8,Fprogramme would be slashed to fund the
OL,9,Fshortfall in defence spending.
OL,11,FHe said: "Surely in 21st century
OL,12,FBritain, people can expect both a
OL,13,Fdecent local hospital and armed forces
OL,14,Fthat keep them safe. So, will the
OL,15,FPrime Minister rule out any cuts to
OL,16,Fthe NHS budget to fund defence?"
OL,18,FStarmer responded by saying that the
OL,19,Fgovernment will "take the necessary
OL,20,Fmeasures to defend our country".
OL,26,@sD@JOUxD@`O]
