OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781111161
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to rule out tax hikes
OL,4,Cto fund defence spending
OL,6,FMeanwhile, ministers have been accused
OL,7,Fof "hiding" when the defence spending
OL,8,Fplans will be published to prevent
OL,9,Fparliamentary scrutiny.
OL,11,FDefence minister Luke Pollard
OL,12,Frepeatedly refused to say whether the
OL,13,Flong-awaited plan would be published
OL,14,Fon Friday outside the House of Commons.
OL,16,FOpposition MPs reacted with fury to
OL,17,Fthe rumoured date, which is a non-
OL,18,Fsitting day, meaning members will not
OL,19,Fbe able to provide scrutiny, with one
OL,20,FTory MP shouting that the minister was
OL,21,F"a disgrace".
OL,26,@oD@DOUoD@KO]}D@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
